\par i) psychological
\par ii) physical
\par iii) both psychological and physical.
\par <#/>When dependence on a drug occurs it is characterised by: 
\par <#/>a. craving (obsessive - compulsive) for the drug, no matter which means is used to get it.
\par <#/>b. drug tolerance - that is need to increase the dose steadily to reach the desired effects.
\par <#/>c. withdrawal symptoms in case of abstinence (withdrawal syndrome or abstinence syndrome).
\par <#/>d. suffering ultimately caused to the drug addict or abuser and to the society as a whole.
\par <h> <#/>SOURCES OF DRUGS </h>
\par <#/>Drugs are either obtained naturally or synthetic (man made).
\par <h> <#/>Natural sources </h>
\par - animals 
\par - moulds and fungi 
\par - microbes.
\par <h> <#/>Preparation </h<
\par <#/>Drugs are prepared and packed in several forms:
